Policy.acknowledgement_statement: Funding support for the Intergenerational Impact of Genetic and Psychological Factors on Blood Pressure study was provided by the National Institute of Nursing Research (R01 NR013520). The dataset(s) used for the analyses described in this manuscript were obtained from the database of Genotypes and Phenotypes (dbGaP) found at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gap through dbGaP accession number XXXX. Genotype and associated phenotype data for the Intergenerational Impact of Genetic and Psychological Factors on Blood Pressure study were provided by Principal Investigators Jacquelyn Taylor, Ph.D., RN, and Cindy Ann Crusto, Ph.D.

ConsentGroup.name: DS-CVD-NPU-MDS-GSO-RD
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction:
Use of the data must be related to Cardiovascular Disease and related disorders. Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations. Use of the data includes methods development research (e.g., development of software or algorithms). Use of the data is limited to genetic studies only.
Hypertension and other cardiovascular-related diseases such as atherosclerosis, arrhythmias, stroke, renal disease, dyslipidemia, heart attack (clotting), heart failure, cardiomyopathy, heart valve and/or circulatory problems and metabolic syndrome.
